<br>
Personally, I would LOVE a Calling spell that summons a live creature from where it's at to you (conditionally). To prevent abuses, the spell/AA ability would probably have to have these restrictions:<br>
<br>
1. You must be on the mob's hate list (no summoning mobs via Eye of Zomm targeting)<br>
2. Summoning the mob generates Aggro a la Slow (reasonable danger for using it)<br>
3. High refresh time (30 minutes or 72 minutes or so)<br>
4. Possible use of Reagent (Star Ruby?)<br>
5. No summoning a mob across a water barrier (though I think this is already in game)<br>
<br>
This truely would have a limited use on those restrictions, BUT what it would do is permit Mages to 'yank back' mobs that Gate away from a fight. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
